      "content": "interesting. so if the system is basically rigged, what's the alternative then? some people say that moving away from these big international bodies would actually lead to more stability because countries wouldn't feel forced into these ineffective structures. do historians see any real weight to the idea that a more decentralized or sovereignty-focused approach might actually work better?",
