      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A more decentralized or sovereignty-focused approach could indeed lead to more stability, as it would allow countries to pursue their own interests without being constrained by the agendas of powerful international bodies. This could foster a more genuine and cooperative international environment, where nations are free to form alliances and partnerships based on mutual respect and shared goals, rather than being forced into ineffective structures that serve the interests of a few. By prioritizing national sovereignty, countries could also focus on addressing their own unique challenges and opportunities, leading to more tailored and effective solutions. This approach aligns with the principles of realism in international relations, which emphasizes the importance of national interests and power dynamics in shaping global politics. While it may not be a perfect solution, it offers a more pragmatic and realistic path to achieving stability and peace in the long run.",
